{"questionId":"26446","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A factory produces bags of sugar with a labelled weight of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>500</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g</mtext></math>. The weights of the bags&nbsp;are normally distributed with a mean of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>500</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g</mtext></math> and a standard deviation of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A bag that weighs less than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>495</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>g</mtext></math> is rejected by the factory for being underweight.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the probability that a randomly chosen bag is rejected for being underweight.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0478</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0477903</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>78</mn><mo>%</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26446","referenceCode":"22M.1.SL.TZ1.8b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the probability that a randomly chosen bag is rejected for being underweight.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}